13 Donhwamun-ro, Gwansu-dong, Jongno-gu, Seoul, South Korea
description: Located in the heart of Seoul, the Seoul Theater has a history of 38 years since it opened in 1978. After the opening, the Seoul Theater has set up 3 theaters, which is the earliest multiplex theater in Korea. Now, it is a multiplex cinema with 7 screening halls. Allegedly, to judge whether a movie is popular in the market, you can only know by its release in the Seoul theater. The Seoul Theater is a mainstream theater with such influence. Movie actors often hold meet-and-greets or autograph sessions here, so if you're lucky, you might be able to meet the characters in the movie! Seoul theaters often show local Korean films. There are fast food restaurants, shops and ice cream parlors in the theater, so you can refuel when you are hungry. There are also many delicious street food stalls in front of the square, such as grilled squid, grilled pufferfish, fried potato chips, etc. It is another fun to buy some to try. There is a spacious lounge on the 4th floor of the theater, providing a place to rest and relax for weary audiences.

description: The Huatan Forest preserves the natural topography and vegetation to the greatest extent possible, and forms forests along the valleys and the foot of the mountain. There are no steps on the walking path, but a low-slope mountain road, which can also be viewed by strollers or wheelchairs. The charm of Huatan Forest is designed to allow nature and people to have a friendly dialogue in any space and any location.
